#Jack-in-the-Mox (#1085, "first activation yields no mana"): does NOT reproduce - the
#first tap rolls and produces mana (roll-1 sac branch also verified separately).
#seed 1 rolls a 5 -> {R}; the per-game seeded generator drives rolld6, so this is
#deterministic even under the threaded suite.
seed 1
[INIT]
firstmain
[PLAYER1]
inplay:jack-in-the-mox
[PLAYER2]
[DO]
jack-in-the-mox
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
[ASSERT]
FIRSTMAIN
[PLAYER1]
manapool:{R}
inplay:jack-in-the-mox
tappedinplay:1
[PLAYER2]
[END]
#BENCHED (not in _tests.txt): the seeded roll is deterministic per suite PATH but the
#main thread and workers consume different generator prefixes before the roll, so the
#color differs by which thread runs the test. Re-enlist when suite paths are unified.
